DIAGNOSIS (
♀
): Body small (1.7 mm), light brown, predominantly smooth and shining, relatively glabrous, with sparse pilosity and setigerous punctures, foamy structures present; head unusually large, vertex highly topped; anterior margin of antennal shelf medially rounded; A1 dilated into flat racquetshaped segment, A2 inserted in upper twothirds of A1, i.e., apical third of A1 forms broad flat horn above insertion of A2; antenna highly specialized, 11­segmented, short, A2–A11 subequal in length to A1, clava 6­ segmented, massive, nonabrupt, subcompact, A11 larger than A10.
